items.description:
Covered Penis LoCon

LoRA request queue on my discord: https://discord.gg/DAfjhRfyEM

This model was trained using 30 images on the NAI model. All of them were nsfw duh.

Recommended weight is 0.9 - 1. This model only works with full body covering outfits like bodystockings or bodysuits, and if youre lucky with pantyhose. Images only used futanari characters, not tested for guys. You can experiment yourself and see what works, but its gonna be a bit random anyways. Works with other character LoRA's if their outfit matches what I said in the last sentence.

Trigger word is covered penis.

Example images were generated using AnyHentai on Euler A with 50 steps and then hires fix. on 0.5 denoising strength.

Note: This was made exclusively on anime images and on an anime checkpoint. Feel free to post images on realistic, semirealistic etc. checkpoints, but do not rate it on that! This was made to be used on anime checkpoints so keep reviews for that!

items.name: Neelam Kothari (80s actress)
items.description:
Neelam Kothari is an Indian actress from the late 80s, early 90s. She was also a Miss India, but played a lot of roles where she was the cute girl next door.

These images have an 80s look to them because the base images were from the 80s and then upscaled without any color correction. I actually like the effect, but understand if it's not for everyone.

Because they were upscaled, the teeth can be a little funny. So recommend suppressing teeth in the negative prompts.

Recommended settings:

  1. Trigger: neelam

  2. CFG Scale: 7-9

  3. Steps: 30

  4. Sampler: DDIM/ UniPC

Please note that this is a LoHa, so it may require additional extensions on A1111

items.name: BeautyFool Reality
items.description:
For v.4.0: This time I trained my model with many more images (1887 to be exact). It is a pruned model. It doesn't require vae but you can use it if you want. Clip skip was trained with 1, but it gives successful results with 2 as well. (I recommend using negative embeddings to avoid burning so you can get great results)

If you want to support my work, you can buy me a coffee. Thanks in advance to those who support.

For v.3.0: Let me describe what I did. I don't speak English, I hope I can explain. All my previous versions were merged models. In this model, I trained three different models with three different folders containing 188 photos, each image having 150 steps (epoch). The photos in the three folders were also different from each other. I couldn't decide which model was the most successful. All three gave very good results. So I finally combined these three models and published them as a single model. So it went through merging first, then training, then merging again. But the most time-consuming and tiring part was the training part. Since I did not have the opportunity to choose both options, I chose this option to emphasize that it has undergone training.

I am sharing the photo package I used for training with you. Those who want can create their own experience by downloading it: link

-*- Let me give you a tip... A model tends to whatever style it was last trained with. You can test it as follows: generate 10-15 times with default settings (20 steps, 7 scale and 512x512 resolution (for 1.5 models)) without writing any negative or positive prompts. (If you want to make the images look clearer, you can write negative prompts provided that you do not use negative embedding). Whichever type of results you got the most in this test, it means that the trend of the model is in that direction -*-

For v1.0: Like my previous anime model, this one consists of several models mixed with each other in certain proportions. I give the list of the mixture below, but I will not specify the mixing ratios. I would like to thank those who created these models.

Absolute Reality

Realistic Vision

CyberRealistic

Pirsus Epic Realism

Ideal for creating ultra-realistic images. Some words can force the model to run nsfw. When the resolution is increased with Hires fix, it creates magnificent visuals. You may have problems with faces in smaller size images. In such cases, you can use adetailer applications such as almostiler.

No need to use vae.

I recommend increasing the resolution by using hires fix instead of using restore faces.

It will continue to be developed.

The models I added to this version were: epicrealism, galaxytimemachines, LRM, etc.

I did not use the Avalon, aresmix and Holygen models that I used in the previous version in this version.

items.name: Broken Covenant Riven | League of Legends
items.description:
LoRA trained on Broken Covenant Riven from League of Legends

requested by: @BangBangFukanawa

Regular Form: broken covenant riven, 1girl, covered eyes, jacket, armor, short hair, red hair

add "mask" if covered eyes fails

Ultimate Form: broken covenant riven, 1girl, long hair, armor, glowing eyes, red hair

Trained on a small dataset, I had to flip and zoom in order to obtain 20 pictures xD

Thats why I recommend using "upper body", as the hands can be a bit tricky sometimes

models used

anime: YesMix - v2.0, MeinaPastel - V6 ( Pastel ), MeinaAlter - V3

2,5D: Aniverse - Aniverse V1.0, PastelDiffusedMix - V2.2, MeinaUnreal - V3

realistic: Paragon V1.0

negative embeddings: bad_prompt, negative_hand, ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, bad-artist, EasyNegative

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realistic models & 2,5D), kl-f8-anime2, blessed2.vae (for anime models)

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras(euler a for img2img upscaling) from time to time im also using DPM++ 2M alt Karras

  • Steps: 20 to 35

  • Clipskip: 2

  • Upscaler : GitHub - pkuliyi2015/multidiffusion-upscaler-for-automatic1111 4x-UltraSharp(for 2,5D & realistic), 4xAnimesharp(for anime)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9 (mostly 7)

  • LORA weight for txt2img: 0.5-1 (for the examples i mostly used 0.8 and 1)

  • Denoise strength upscaling: 0.3 to 0.55

If you want to autocomplete the tags & trigger im using, I recommend using Booru style tag autocompletion for AUTOMATIC1111's Stable Diffusion web UI

For full body shots i recommend using: ComfyUI Impact Pack

or the a1111 alternative GitHub - Bing-su/adetailer

items.name: Lewd poses for OpenPose / Canny Controlnet
items.description:
If you like what I do please consider supporting me on Patreon and contributing your ideas to my future projects!

These poses are to be used with Openpose and Canny TOGETHER.

First enable openpose in a controlnet unit and load the pose without a preprocessor and hit the little red button.

Next enable another controlnet unit and load canny without a preprocessor and hit the little red button.

1 Openpose + 1 Canny = lewds.


If the pose isn't turning out the way you want it try lowering the Ending Control Step and/or the Control Weight.

If your model is clipping outside of your image it might be because you are using a different aspect ratio then what was used to make the pose. Try using a similar aspect ratio.

Included with the openpose and canny files are example images, .json files for editing the poses, and tags you can include in the prompt written in the names of the example images.

I used Dreamshaper and Azovya photoreal for testing.

There are 16 poses total in this archive.

items.name: Puffy Guofeng
items.description:
Merge of the Puffy and Guofeng models. I did not make either of the source models or alter the source models with additional training data. These models are harsh, rough, and unrefined. These models are posted to show variations in different merge techniques and more will be added. If these models could be utilized in any way I would be happy, but these may also be useless. Please leave any feedback.

Please give your support to the original models found here:
Puffy v2.0
https://civitai.com/models/31262/puffy
Guofeng v3.4
https://civitai.com/models/10415/3-guofeng3

Check model details for each version and the results I produced with these. Some mix's are better than others. All of them produce very beautiful women.

items.name: Style Gravity Magic
items.description:
This is my seventh publicly released Textual Inversion, called Style-Gravitymagic. This model was trained on a single image of a generated black hole using DreamArtist. This TI gives things a very vibrant colorful, starry, and magical feel. A lot of images will feature a magical starry circular shape or have characters trying to hold magical energy sources.

The strength of the TI output depends on the prompt used and can range from subtle to overwhelming. It's important to adjust the weights or where you put the TI in the order of the prompt.

items.name: Chichi (Older LOCON version) - Dragon Ball Z
items.description:
I continue evading the cleaning of that new dataset. Instead i dusted this one, cleaned it again, added some extra costume images and re tagged it. Thus this shares the dataset with my Chichi V2 Lora

Works fine with: <lyco:chichi_dbzV3:0.7> chichi_dbz, <outfit>

I added triggers for the following outfits:

  • Purple_Dress_Orange_Neckerchief: Variation of her normal attire in purple and red.

  • Chichi_Bikini_Armor: Chichi cosplaying as her self in her Bikini armor.

  • Chichi_Blue_China_Dress: Her DB tournament arc dress look alike. I don't remember her using it during her MILF days but i found images and i liked it. Her MILF version of the attire is pants less of course.

  • Yellow_China_Dress_Purple_Neckerchief: Variation of her normal attire in yellow and purple. This probably need to add Neckerchief as extra or in negative as most of the images didn't have it and it is iffy. Sadly couldn't make this one consistent as it seems to fight against the top of her dress and turns it into a ribbon.

As Always I'll add the dataset so people can check the tag summary and experiment.

items.name: Valkyrie Drive Mermaid - Mamori Tokonome
items.description:
This is my first lora! I trained with anylora on colab.

I'll update this to improve it later, as this was just a test to see if it was possible with 28 pictures of her from episode 1. There's only portrait pictures, but as you can see, all you need to do is tell it you want a full body shot and put portrait in negatives and then just inpaint her face and hair on full strength and it will fix it.

Her hair pin will not get much better from inpainting at this time. It's a really simple fix that even a non artist can fix if you wanna just draw it in. In the anime, the hair pin isn't very consistent, so I'll need to train again later on and draw the pin myself for the training to be able to up scale it and actually make it look how it's meant to.

You can upscale the images to 550x550, and you will get an all NANs error if you try to go higher because there are no higher res images in the data set yet.

The hands leave a lot to be desired, but you can always use controlnet to make it better. I'll upload improved images next time when I update this.

  • Hair pin lacks a lot to be desired

  • I will need to tag the backgrounds next time so that the backgrounds don't default to the same nature background

  • If you think about the hands, you will have a curse on your household. Please use controlnet to correct them for now.

  2. 另外建议使用negative embedding 比如： 16-token-negative-deliberate-neg，realisticvision-negative-embedding

Landscape design-related Lora can be mainly used to generate urban landscape pictures and add landscape elements in architectural and urban design scenes. This model is not trained by a single type of landscape, and the control of the design style is not precise. It is recommended to be used as an auxiliary.

  1. It is recommended to use it with my published RealisticUrbanMix or other urban models;

  2. In addition, it is recommended to use negative embedding such as: 16-token-negative-deliberate-neg, realisticvision-negative-embedding

items.name: Minustype_RealisticUrbanMix
items.description:
城市相关的全要素Lora，在大量的高分辨率效果图上进行分类训练，同时由多个模型融合而成，有较强的泛化能力，适用于大多数与建筑、城市设计相关的生成场景。对于特殊的场景搭配专用的lora和提示词表现会更好。

使用建议：

  1. 建议生成尺寸较大的图像，长边768像素以上；

  2. 可以搭配我公开的其他lora模型，但因为训练集部分的重合需要根据情况降低权重，一般不超过0.3，其他主题的lora则需要根据实际情况调整

  3. 另外建议使用negative embedding 比如： 16-token-negative-deliberate-neg，realisticvision-negative-embedding

  4. 实质上本模型是RealisticUrbanMix没有查分之前的版本，所以可以使用其他底模搭配RealisticUrbanMix获得相似的效果，或者直接搭配RealisticUrbanMix以达到调整风格强度的效果

The city-related full-element Lora is trained on a large number of high-resolution renderings, and is composed of multiple models at the same time. It has strong generalization ability and is suitable for most generation scenarios related to architecture and urban design. For special scenes, it will perform better with dedicated lora and prompt words.

Recommendations:

It is recommended to generate an image with a larger size, with a long side of 768 pixels or more;

It can be used with other lora models that I disclosed, but because of the overlap of the training set part, the weight needs to be reduced according to the situation, generally no more than 0.3, and the lora of other topics needs to be adjusted according to the actual situation In addition,

It is recommended to use negative embedding such as: 16-token-negative-deliberate-neg, realisticvision-negative-embedding

In essence, this model is the version before RealisticUrbanMix did not check the score, so you can use other base models with RealisticUrbanMix to achieve similar effects, or directly match with RealisticUrbanMix to achieve the effect of adjusting the style intensity
